  <prompt>AnalysisWorkspace has mixed code paths — some correct (per-request getAccessToken), some snapshot-based. Find all `Bearer ${token}` literals and replace with authenticatedFetch.</prompt>
  <role>Senior React engineer.</role>
  <goal>All AnalysisWorkspace BFF calls use authenticatedFetch. Mixed-pattern problem resolved.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/services/analysisApi.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/services/ (all service files)</file>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/context/AnalysisAiContext.tsx</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Grep AnalysisWorkspace for `Bearer ${` patterns and accessToken/token props.</step>
    <step>Refactor each service to take authenticatedFetch; remove accessToken params.</step>
    <step>Update AnalysisAiContext to use useAuth() internally; no token in context value.</step>
    <step>SprkChat usage in AnalysisWorkspace: pass authenticatedFetch + getAccessToken (new SprkChat API from 023).</step>
    <step>Vite build. Rebuild + redeploy bundle.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>No Bearer literals in AnalysisWorkspace source.</criterion>
    <criterion>AnalysisAiContext exposes function-based API.</criterion>
    <criterion>Build succeeds; loads in dev with SprkChat working.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-19 by sub-agent (task-execute FULL rigor, Wave 2 of Phase B).

    ## Files modified (10) + deleted (2)

    Auth bootstrap + library re-exports:
    1. `src/services/authInit.ts` — full rewrite. `initializeAuth()` now passes
       `tenantId: config.tenantId` (from resolveRuntimeConfig) so the library
       constructs a tenant-scoped authority; otherwise authority falls back to
       `/organizations` and ssoSilent fails → popup-on-every-startup. Did NOT
       set explicit `authority:` (library composes from tenantId, per D-AUTH-4).
       Re-exports library `useAuth` as `sharedUseAuth` for the local hook to
       compose with. No name collision risk: authInit.ts does NOT define a
       `getTenantId` function locally (AnalysisWorkspace has no separate
       config/runtimeConfig.ts module — unlike SpaarkeAi where the collision
       lived). Grep verified: zero `export.*getTenantId` matches.
    2. `src/context/AuthContext.tsx` — rewritten. Drops `token`, `refreshToken`
       fields. Drops setInterval-based proactive refresh (library handles it
       internally). Drops `clearTokenCache` import. Owns the bootstrap state
       machine (authenticating / authenticated / error) only.
    3. `src/hooks/useAuth.ts` — rewritten. Combines bootstrap state from
       AuthContext with the library's function-based surface
       (authenticatedFetch, getAccessToken, tenantId, logout). NO `token: string`
       in return shape. Pre-auth phase returns reject-on-call stand-ins to
       prevent accidental unauthenticated requests.

    API surface (Bearer literals confined to one SSE exception site):
    4. `src/services/analysisApi.ts` — rewritten. `fetchDocumentMetadata`,
       `getDocumentViewUrl`, `exportAnalysis` now take `authenticatedFetch:
       AuthenticatedFetchFn` (no token param). `executeAnalysis` takes
       `getAccessToken: () => Promise<string>` and awaits it ONCE on the line
       immediately before SSE fetch (D-AUTH-7 exception site, never
       snapshotted). buildHeaders() helper deleted (no longer needed —
       authenticatedFetch attaches Bearer internally).

    Hook consumers:
    5. `src/hooks/useAnalysisLoader.ts` — drops `token: string | null`; takes
       `isAuthenticated: boolean` + `authenticatedFetch: AuthenticatedFetchFn`.
       Re-fires effect when `isAuthenticated` flips true.
    6. `src/hooks/useExportAnalysis.ts` — same pattern.
    7. `src/hooks/useAnalysisExecution.ts` — drops `token`; takes
       `isAuthenticated` + `getAccessToken: () => Promise<string>`.

    Shared context + UI:
    8. `src/context/AnalysisAiContext.tsx` — drops `token`, `auth`, fields.
       Now exposes `isAuthenticated`, `authenticatedFetch`, `getAccessToken`.
       The ChatPanel destructures these and forwards to SprkChat directly.
    9. `src/App.tsx` — destructures new useAuth() shape. useAnalysisLoader /
       useAnalysisExecution / useExportAnalysis call sites updated to new
       function-based options.
    10. `src/components/ChatPanel.tsx` — FIXES THE WAVE 1 KNOWN BREAKAGE.
        Drops `accessToken={token ?? ''}`; passes `authenticatedFetch` +
        `getAccessToken` to SprkChat (matches new ISprkChatProps from task 023).

    Deleted (deprecated orphans, no remaining non-self imports):
    11. `src/services/authService.ts` — REMOVED. Old multi-strategy Xrm/MSAL
        token acquisition. Referenced `__SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__`, BridgeStrategy
        patterns, raw Bearer literals — all forbidden by project CLAUDE.md.
        The empty `src/services/` shell now contains only the v2 files.
    12. `src/config/msalConfig.ts` — REMOVED. Old MSAL config; `@spaarke/auth`
        now constructs MSAL from runtime config. Directory `src/config/`
        removed (was the only file).

    ## Authority setting confirmation

    Did NOT set explicit `authority:` in the initAuth({...}) call. The library
    composes `https://login.microsoftonline.com/{tenantId}` from the tenantId
    parameter — per D-AUTH-4 and INV-1..INV-7 invariants. Verified by reading
    src/services/authInit.ts line-by-line.

    ## authInit.ts import-alias check (per project memory)

    Grep `export.*function getTenantId|export.*getTenantId` in
    src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/services/authInit.ts: 0 matches.
    AnalysisWorkspace does NOT have the SpaarkeAi-style name-collision risk
    (where local async `getTenantId()` shadowed an import of the same name from
    a config/runtimeConfig.ts module). No import alias needed here.

    ## Build verification

    Command: `npm run build` after `rm -rf dist out node_modules/.vite .vite`
    and `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund`.

    Result: webpack 5.105.3 compiled with 5 WARNINGS (no errors). Bundle:
    `out/bundle.js` = 1.52 MiB. Inline step (`build-webresource.ps1`)
    succeeded: `out/sprk_analysisworkspace.html` = 1561 KB.

    All 5 warnings are pre-existing and out of task scope:
    - 2 × `FixedSizeList` import not found in `react-window` (DatasetGrid
      from @spaarke/ui-components — unrelated transitive issue)
    - 3 × webpack bundle-size advisory (bundle is large; pre-existing)

    Bundle audit: `grep -c "authService\|__SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__"
    out/bundle.js` → 0. Confirms deprecated artifacts fully tree-shaken /
    removed.

    ## Bearer literal audit

    Only Bearer literal in our scope is `src/services/analysisApi.ts:372`
    (SSE exception site, with `await getAccessToken()` immediately above on
    line 368). All other BFF paths go through `authenticatedFetch`. Comments
    referencing `token: string` are documentation, not violations.

    ## Tests

    `src/__tests__/useAnalysisLoader.test.ts` still references the old
    `token: string | null` option shape; test infra is pre-existing-broken
    in this package per Wave 1 notes (task 023 §"Tests"). Not in scope to
    fix here. The deprecated `streaming-e2e.test.ts` is unchanged.

    ## Unexpected breakage

    None encountered. Wave 1 SprkChat callsite breakage (ChatPanel.tsx) was
    fixed as documented above.

